 CLASS SKILL-QUEST</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>A rogue would have to know when to sneak/hide around some things, use Sense Traps (else have the trap break their hide like the SolA trap), be able to do some sneak pulling on some greens (lest they be mobbed by a ton of greens), have their lockpick skills maxed to get through, and maybe a necessary mob susceptible to a specific poison. In all, not much XP for the quest, but a good place to sharpen your skills. Now with SoL, maybe a skill-specific item (+% Backstab) at the end of it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=urazragingfists>Uraz Ragingfists</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 6:10:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Creative ideas to make the game better</span><hr size=1> I have no idea, but i do think that questing should be more about testing you/making you a better player than testing your patience cause you gotta camp rare_mob_01 for 16 hours to get a rock to hand into a guy so Tougher_than_you_mob_01 spawns. but that sounds good, sounds very RPGish<br><br>Uraz<br><br>EDIT:Spelling blah<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=urazragingfists>Uraz Ragingfists</A> at: 2/6/02 6:11:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=simplee>Simplee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 7:41:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Creative ideas to make the game better</span><hr size=1> Good ideas on improvements. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I have one pet peeve with this game. Remember the ol' Crushbone belt quest? It worked so well that people &lt;looks guilty&gt; use it to get their twinks past those awkward young years? That quest had incredible exp from turning in those belts. (Well, incredible if you were so young you have to have an escort to Kaladim) What kind of exp. increase do you get for doing quests when you are older?... nuttin. There are some really cool sounding quests out there, but who is gonna do 'em if the exp. bar doesn't even wiggle. <br><br>I would like to see the quests give exp. in the higher levels too. I'm not suggesting a level 50 should be able to use cb belts to get that exp. cushion, but on higher level quests it would be nice to see the bar.. MOVE.<br><br>Just my 2cp.<br><br>Simplee <br>Torvus'vir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mav>Mav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 10:48:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Creative ideas to make the game better</span><hr size=1> Great topic.  I have always been very disappointed with what EQ calls quests.  First of all, they are all static quests and most of them are unsolvable just using in game information.  When I first started playing I turned /ooc off and refused to peek at a spoiler site because I wanted to &quot;conquer the quest&quot;.  After much trial and error I found I had to turn /ooc on and listen to ppl asking questions about the quests and eventually go to the spoiler sites.  After that the quests became &quot;do A, go to X, say Y, get reward&quot;.  I really felt cheated out of the experience.  When I began gaming one of the first games was Zork and when you figured out the riddle or rationalized out the problem..it was a rush when the door opened.<br><br>Today you go to sites where you see the quests rated and all of the ratings are based on the loot you get, not the thrill of the accomplishment.  Wish I had an answer...I'd be rich...well not rich enuf to play on Legends but I could get 6-pack.<br><br>I love EQ for what it is...I hate it for what it could be.<br><br>Mav. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uveenublue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>veenublue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/8/02 2:59:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.phank.com/avitars/smallavitar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Creative ideas to make the game better</span><hr size=1> Let me just add my frustration on the quest I am working on now. A nice little quest (you can see more in the quest section) where you run little errands as a cool spy (a level 4 could do this.) Then all of a sudden you have to kill level 60 mobs in MASS. Nice ramping. I would like to see more creative and less farming. Also a nice difficulty ramp. Grr. Makes me mad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ujalizarinkrymzyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalizarin Krymzyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RAWR!</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/8/02 3:16:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> zork!</span><hr size=1> lol, i remember Zork...what a fun game!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udainbornhald.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dain Bornhald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/8/02 7:55:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: zork!</span><hr size=1> They should bring AA abilities down to the lower levels.  But instead of getting more points by Exp, offer them in &quot;One time use only&quot; quests that permanently raise ability points.  Every freakin single quest in EQ ultimately results in a new weapon or armor or stat altering item.  Make the quest take a long time but not &quot;gotta kill a dragon&quot; hard.  And if stat points is too powerful then add in quests that will increase abilities(like smithing or jewelcrafting) by so many points, rather than having to make 'item a' over and over until it is trivial, then move on to 'item b'.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=frodoj>FrodoJ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/10/02 6:51:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> umm</span><hr size=1> sounds like a tedious verant like idea - see plane of mischief,nerf nerf nerf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usomberlainwayfaerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somberlain Wayfaerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Underwear Gnome Handler</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/11/02 8:42:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> VI contact</span><hr size=1> Does anyone know of any way to contact VI with suggestions without posting them on the EQ message board?  As in an email address?  Rather than more expansions, I've got some ideas for more freebie zones that could be added to the Old World, and have even come up with a lot of mob, quest and item ideas that would make it worthwhile.  But if I type it all up (we're talking pages and pages, plus maps), I am not posting it on a board somewhere.<br><br>Just curious.<br><br><br> <p>Somberlain Wayfaerer<BR>Wanderer of Druzzil Ro<BR>Guild Leader of the Justice Knights<BR><a href="http://www.geocities.com/justiceknights/jk.html">www.geocities.com/justiceknights</a> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uetelka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Etelka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/11/02 11:16:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2137.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI contact</span><hr size=1> Tossing in my 2 cp again..<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;How about reserving a certain zone AT Verant instead of on a message board?<br>I mean, why is there only one zone at a certain time, when we are only talking about discspace here? If you could just mail Verant, or petition, a reservation like &lt;I want an extra Hate plane up next week from 8 PM till midnight for 60 people, will give the names later.&gt; this entire problem will not exist any more. A lot of this can be automated too, so, if done correctly, maintenance will stay pretty low.<br>I'm sure there would be quite a bit of development work necessary, but it would resolve 90 percent of all that high-level mess we've seen on these boards lately.<br>This would seriously change things like the economy of the game by the way, as primal gear would be as common as peridots in a few years... &quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>This idea, as posted before, has one thing in common with Lannella's one: in that the main focus is on reducing the tension between different players. Mine on the raid/interguild level, Lanella's on the team/inter-class level, as this idea of hers seems to intend forcing people to understand their (twinke